                            <comment id="14965418" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 17:21:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user StephanEwen opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1275&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1275&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2880&quot; title=&quot;Allow DeserializationSchema to throw IOException in deserialization method&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2880&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2880&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;streaming&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;API-Breaking&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Allow DeserializationSchema to forward exceptions&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The DeserializationSchema is now allowed to forward exceptions on deserialization.&lt;br/&gt;
    This is useful because many non-trivial decoders (Flink&apos;s TypeSerializers, Avro, etc) may throw exceptions. Otherwise, this leads to clumly catching and nesting of exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;


